import { View, Text,TouchableOpacity } from 'react-native'
import React from 'react'
import Icon from 'react-native-vector-icons/FontAwesome';
import { useNavigation } from "@react-navigation/native";
export default function BottomTab() {
    const navigation = useNavigation();
  return (
    <View className="position-sticky bg-[#EEEEEE] w-100">
      <View className="flex-row w-100 px-2  justify-between">
        <TouchableOpacity className="flex-column"
        onPress={()=>navigation.navigate('Home')}
        >
          <View className="ml-2">
            <Icon name="home" size={26} color="black" />
          </View>
          <Text>Home</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
        <TouchableOpacity className="flex-column"
        onPress={()=>navigation.navigate('HistoryScreen')}
        >
          <View className="ml-2">
            <Icon name="search" size={26} color="black" />
          </View>
          <Text>History</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
        <TouchableOpacity className="flex-column">
          <View className="ml-2">
            <Icon name="user" size={26} color="black" />
          </View>
          <Text>Profile</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
        <TouchableOpacity className="flex-column">
          <View className="ml-2">
            <Icon name="navicon" size={26} color="black" />
          </View>
          <Text>Menu</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
      </View>
    </View>
  );
}
